<h2>Conversion Rates and Traffic Quality</h2>
<p><strong>15. AI search traffic converts at 4.4x the rate of traditional organic traffic.</strong> Visitors from AI platforms arrive with higher intent. (Source: <a href="https://www.growthmarshal.io/field-notes/ai-search-traffic-is-4x-more-valuable-than-organic">Semrush</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>16. Ahrefs found AI visitors convert at 23x the rate of organic visitors.</strong> 0.5% of total visitors from AI drove 12.1% of signups. (Source: <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog">Ahrefs</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>17. ChatGPT ecommerce traffic converts 31% higher than non-branded organic search.</strong> (Source: <a href="https://searchengineland.com/chatgpt-vs-non-branded-organic-search-conversions-470321">Search Engine Land / Visibility Labs</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>18. AI-referred visitors spend 68% more time on websites than organic visitors.</strong> Session duration averages 9+ minutes from Perplexity referrals. (Source: <a href="https://seranking.com/blog/ai-traffic-research-study/">SE Ranking</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>19. Claude referrals have the highest average session value at $4.56 per visit.</strong> Perplexity follows at $3.12. ChatGPT averages $2.34. (Source: <a href="https://superprompt.com/blog/ai-traffic-up-527-percent-how-to-get-cited-by-chatgpt-claude-perplexity-2025">Superprompt</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>20. ChatGPT-sourced B2B visitors have double the session duration of average visitors.</strong> They also show 33% higher conversion rates. (Source: <a href="https://www.siegemedia.com/strategy/chatgpt-referral-traffic-data">Siege Media</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>21. AI referrals convert at 11.4% vs 5.3% for organic across global ecommerce.</strong> (Source: <a href="https://almcorp.com/blog/chatgpt-vs-organic-search-conversion-rate/">Similarweb via ALM Corp</a>, 2026)</p>
<p>These conversion rates matter because AI traffic is not just growing. It is growing with higher intent. For tips on tracking this traffic, see our guide on <a href="/blog/track-ai-search-visibility/">how to track AI search visibility</a>.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="AI overviews and zero-click search impact statistics" src="/images/blog/ai-overviews-zero-click-impact.webp" /></p>
<h2>AI Overviews and Zero-Click Impact</h2>
<p><strong>22. Google AI Overviews appear on 48% of all search queries as of March 2026.</strong> Up from 13.14% in March 2025 and 34.5% in December 2025. (Source: <a href="https://www.stackmatix.com/blog/google-ai-overview-seo-impact">Stackmatix</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>23. AI Overviews reduce organic CTR by 61%.</strong> Click-through rates dropped from 1.76% to 0.61% for queries showing AI Overviews. (Source: <a href="https://www.seerinteractive.com/insights/aio-impact-on-google-ctr-september-2025-update">Seer Interactive</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>24. 93% of AI search sessions end without a website click.</strong> Only 7% of sessions result in a referral to an external site. (Source: <a href="https://www.superlines.io/articles/ai-search-statistics/">Semrush</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>25. Zero-click searches reached 58.5% of all US searches in 2025.</strong> That rate rises to 83% when AI Overviews are present. (Source: <a href="https://thedigitalbloom.com/learn/2025-organic-traffic-crisis-analysis-report/">The Digital Bloom</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>26. Brands cited in AI Overviews earn 35% more organic clicks.</strong> They also earn 91% more paid clicks. Being cited offsets the CTR drop. (Source: <a href="https://www.searchenginejournal.com/impact-of-ai-overviews-how-publishers-need-to-adapt/556843/">Search Engine Journal</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>27. Organic click share dropped 11 to 23 percentage points across every vertical.</strong> This decline accelerated in Q1 2026. (Source: <a href="https://thedigitalbloom.com/learn/organic-traffic-crisis-report-2026-update/">The Digital Bloom</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>28. 75% of Google AI Mode sessions end without external site visits.</strong> AI Mode is even more zero-click than standard AI Overviews. (Source: <a href="https://www.superlines.io/articles/ai-search-statistics/">Superlines</a>, 2026)</p>
<p>The zero-click trend is real. But websites cited in AI responses gain traffic while others lose it. Learn how to <a href="/blog/optimize-google-ai-overviews/">optimize for Google AI Overviews</a> and <a href="/blog/zero-click-search-seo/">reduce the impact of zero-click searches</a>.</p>
