<h2>Industry-Specific AI Traffic</h2>
<p><strong>29. Legal websites see the highest AI referral traffic share at 1.34% of total sessions.</strong> That share grew 823% year over year. (Source: <a href="https://superprompt.com/blog/ai-traffic-up-527-percent-how-to-get-cited-by-chatgpt-claude-perplexity-2025">Superprompt</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>30. Finance sites receive 1.21% of traffic from AI referrals.</strong> Growth rate: 612% year over year. (Source: <a href="https://superprompt.com/blog/ai-traffic-up-527-percent-how-to-get-cited-by-chatgpt-claude-perplexity-2025">Superprompt</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>31. Healthcare sites get 0.89% of traffic from AI platforms.</strong> Growth rate: 445% year over year. (Source: <a href="https://superprompt.com/blog/ai-traffic-up-527-percent-how-to-get-cited-by-chatgpt-claude-perplexity-2025">Superprompt</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>32. The IT industry experiences the highest AI-driven visit share at 2.8% of total traffic.</strong> (Source: <a href="https://www.asklantern.com/blogs/chatgpt-drives-87-of-ai-referral-traffic">Conductor</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>33. Legal, finance, health, SMB, and insurance account for 55% of all LLM-sourced sessions.</strong> These 5 verticals dominate AI referral traffic. (Source: <a href="https://searchengineland.com/ai-traffic-up-seo-rewritten-459954">Search Engine Land</a>, 2025)</p>
<p><strong>34. 40% to 55% of buyers in consumer electronics, travel, and financial services use AI search for purchase decisions.</strong> (Source: <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/ai-seo-statistics/">Semrush</a>, 2026)</p>
<p><strong>35. 34% of B2B SaaS companies block AI crawlers via robots.txt.</strong> They are removing themselves from AI search results entirely. (Source: <a href="https://beomniscient.com/blog/b2b-seo-statistics/">Omniscient Digital</a>, 2026)</p>
